#### 1. Tng quan qua cc ch s thng k

  • Min = 12: Thp nht l 12, v mt y hc th BMI di ~13 l rt thp (c th gp mt s trng hp suy dinh dng hay d liu ngoi lai).
  • 1st Qu. = 24: Phn v th nht xp x 24, ngng cn trn ca bnh thng (18.524.9).
  • Median = 27: Trung v BMI l 27, ri vo nhm overweight (2529.9).
  • Mean = 28.38: Trung bnh BMI cao hn trung v, cho thy phn phi lch phi (right-skewed).
  • 3rd Qu. = 31: Phn v th ba l 31, nm trong khong bo ph cp 1 (30).
  • Max = 98: Mc ti a ln ti 98, r rng l mt gi tr ngoi lai cc ln, khng nh c mt s lng t ngi vi BMI rt cao.

chnh lch gia Mean (28.38) v Median (27) (~1.4 n v) khng qu ln, nhng phn ui phi (right tail) rt di v m c outlier (th hin r Boxplot) khin phn phi tr nn mt i xng.

2. Phn phi BMI (Histogram + Density)

  1. Dng phn phi:
    • Histogram cho thy mt nh (mode) nm gn 2526.
    • Phn phi lch phi (right-skewed) r rt; pha phi (cc gi tr ln) gim dn nhng ko di n tn 70, 80, 90, thm ch 98.
  2. So snh vi ng mt (blue line): ng mt trng khp vi vic c mt nh khong 2526 v gim dc khi BMI > 30, tuy nhin vn b di v bn phi.
  3. Mi tng quan MeanMedian:
    • Mean (28.38) > Median (27) ph hp vi skew phi.
    • Gi tr 25 (ng vch t ) l ngng overweight, v r rng mt b phn ln dn s kho st nm pha trn ngng ny.

3. Boxplot of BMI

  1. V tr hp d liu:
    • Hp (box) nm trong khong [24, 31] (tc Q1Q3), vi Median = 27.
    • Khong IQR = 31 24 = 7, khng qu ln so vi ton thang o, nhng do c nhiu outlier pha trn nn khi tnh phm vi (upper fence) bng \(Q3 + 1.5*IQR = 31 + 1.5\times 7 = 31 + 10.5 = 41.5\), vn cn rt nhiu gi tr BMI > 41.5 c xp thnh outlier.
  2. Outliers cc ln: Ta thy rt nhiu im nm ri rc t 45, 50, 60 n 98. iu ny cho thy phn phi lch phi km theo ui rt di, to ra mt lot gi tr ngoi lai.
  3. ngha thc tin:
    • V y t cng cng, BMI > 30 (bo ph) l nhm nguy c, cao hn na nh 40, 50, 60 l bo ph bnh l (morbid obesity).
    • R rng, mu d liu gm nhiu c nhn ang gp tnh trng tha cn, bo ph nng.

4. QQ Plot (Phn phi so vi Normal)

Quan st QQ plot, ta thy: 1. Khc gia: D liu di gia (khong 2035) cong ln, sau b cong mnh ra khi ng cho l thuyt.
2. Phn ui di (BMI rt thp) nm pha trn ng l thuyt tail tri khng qu di (v c th c mt vi outlier thp ~12).
3. Phn ui trn (BMI rt cao) vt hn ln khi ng chun, cho thy s phnh to ca ui phi nng outlier bn phi.

Tng th, QQ plot xc nhn BMI khng tun theo phn phi chun (normal distribution), m lch phi rt r.

5. Mt s gi x l thng k / tin x l

  1. Loi b hoc x l outliers:
    • Cc gi tr BMI cc cao (70, 80, 90) c th nh hng mnh n mt s m hnh nhy cm vi outliers (v d: linear regression).
    • Trc khi lm m hnh (nht l classification), ta cn nhc:
      • Loi b outliers bng quy tc IQR (nu cm thy l d liu sai st hoc qu him).
      • Hoc gi li nu l d liu tht, v trong y khoa, cc trng hp BMI > 40 thc ra vn c t l mc tiu ng, bnh tim mch cao, nn c gi tr d bo.
  2. Bin i (transformation):
    • C th th log transform (log(BMI)) hoc power transform gim lch phi. Tuy nhin, BMI vn l ch s c tnh t cn nng/chiu cao, nn vic log-transform c th khin din gii lm sng kh hn.
    • Hoc s dng robust scaling (a median v 0, IQR v 1) bt nh hng ca outliers.
  3. Binning / Discretization:
    • Ph bin trong nghin cu lm sng, BMI thng chia thnh nhm: underweight (<18.5), normal (18.524.9), overweight (2529.9), obese I (3034.9), obese II (3539.9), obese III (40).
    • Vic chia nhm c th gip m hnh d x l hn, nht l m hnh tree-based, ng thi d gii thch v mt y hc (phn loi nguy c).

  • Min = 0, Q1 = 0, Median = 0: iu ny cho thy hn 50% (thc t l >50%) gi tr trong d liu l 0 ngy mental health not good. Ni cch khc, mt b phn ln ngi tham gia khng gp vn g v sc kho tinh thn trong 30 ngy qua (hoc h ghi nhn l 0).
  • Mean = 3.185: Trung bnh li cao hn hn so vi median = 0, chng t phn phi b lch phi rt mnh (right-skewed), v c mt s lng ng k ngi c nhiu ngy mental health not good.
  • Q3 = 2: Tc 75% d liu c s ngy 2.
  • Max = 30: C ngi bo co ti a 30 ngy gp vn v sc kho tinh thn, cng c th xem l outlier (nhng v mt thc tin th vn xy ra).

Nh vy, a s mu nm 0 (khng ngy gp vn ), cn mt nhm nh c gi tr rt cao (ti 30 ngy).

2. Phn phi Mental Health (Histogram)

  1. Hin tng spike ti 0
    • Trn histogram, ct 0 (ngha l 0 ngy not good) p o, chim phn ln mu.
    • Sau , tn sut gim cc nhanh khi s ngy tng ln.
    • Mt s cm nh xut hin 12 ngy, 35 ngy, v.v v mt s t trng hp vt ln 30 ngy.
  2. Dng phn phi ri (count data)
    • Bin ny c th l bin m (integer t 0 n 30).
    • Rt nhiu zero gi kh nng zero-inflated hoc ht sc lch phi.

3. Boxplot of Mental Health

  1. V tr hp:
    • Do Q1 = 0, Median = 0 v Q3 = 2, nn hp (box) st y, tp trung gn 02.
    • IQR = Q3 Q1 = 2 0 = 2, kh nh so vi ton thang o (030).
  2. Outliers dy c:
    • Whisker trn (upper fence) thng c tnh l Q3 + 1.5*IQR = 2 + 1.5*2 = 5. Vy nn bt c gi tr > 5 u b xem l outlier theo nh ngha boxplot.
    • Quan st cho thy c rt nhiu im t 6 n 30 (nht l cm 30) vn thnh mt ct outlier ko di thng ln.

4. QQ Plot

  1. Phn ln gi tr 0: QQ plot cho thy mt di phng gn 0, do qu nhiu quan st bng 0.
  2. ui phi vt rt cao:
    • Khi >5, s ngy mental health tng v ngy cng chch khi ng thng chun.
    • on trn cng (gn 30), ta thy nhiu im nm st nhau, cng bc l r s lch phi v khng tng thch vi phn phi chun.
  3. Tm li: D liu hon ton khng tun theo normal distribution. Thay vo , n ging mt bin m (count) c s lng 0 rt ln (zero-inflated) v mt ui phi ko di.

5. H qu v gi phn tch

  1. Khng dng gi nh normal
    • D liu ny khng thch hp p dng trc tip cc m hnh/kim nh i hi phn phi chun.
    • Nu phn tch tng quan (chng hn vi Pearson), kt qu c th sai lch.
  2. Bin i d liu
    • Log-transform (v d \(\log(x+1)\)) hay sqrt-transform c th gim bt lch. Nhng vn phi ch bn cht ri rc (count) v vic 0 chim p o.
    • i khi, m hnh Poisson hay Negative Binomial (hoc zero-inflated versions) mi ph hp nu ta cn modeling bin ny nh mt bin ph thuc.
  3. Phn nhm (binning)
    • Trong cc bi ton classification, ta thng chia mental health days thnh cc nhm ngha:
      • Khng ngy (0)
      • Vi ngy (12, 35, )
      • Nhiu ngy (14, hoc 20, 30) tu mc tiu.
    • Cch ny gip x l tnh trng zero-inflation v d din gii trong lm sng (v d >=14 ngy thng c xp nhm nng).
  4. Xc thc outliers hay khng: Cc gi tr 30 ngy c th l hon ton hp l v mt lm sng (ngi b trm cm dai dng sut thng). Khng nht thit loi b, m nn x l bng m hnh thng k ph hp.

1. Quan st mi quan h: BMI ~ MentHlth v BMI ~ PhysHlth

1.1 Boxplot/Violin plot: BMI theo MentHlth (hoc PhysHlth)

  • Dng phn phi BMI gn nh ging nhau hu ht cc bin ca MentHlth/PhysHlth. Tc median ca BMI mi bin u xoay quanh ~2526, IQR cng xp x 78 n v (khong [2230]) v v s outlier vn ln ti 80100.
  • Khng thy xu hng tng/gim r rt ca BMI khi MentHlth/PhysHlth tng. Vn c dao ng nh median (v d bin MentHlth=0 c median ~25, bin MentHlth=30 c median ~26), nhng chnh lch khng qu ng k so vi tri rng chung.

T , c v khng c mi lin h mnh gia s ngy sc khe tinh thn/th cht km vi ch s BMI. Ni cch khc, mi mc MentHlth/PhysHlth, ta u gp loi BMI t thp (1520) n rt cao (70100).

1.2 Scatter plot: BMI ~ MentHlth (hoc PhysHlth)

  • Cc scatter plot cho thy mt mng dy vng BMI ~25 v MentHlth/PhysHlth = 0 (v rt nhiu quan st 0 ngy km).
  • Khi MentHlth/PhysHlth tng, BMI vn phn b tri rng 15100, khng thu hp hay dch chuyn nhiu.
  • ng hi quy (mu ) th hin dc (slope) hi dng nhng rt nh gi nu c tng quan th cng yu (r-value c th rt thp).

Kt lun s b:

BMI hu nh khng tng quan mnh vi MentHlth hay PhysHlth; mi nhm ngy km vn c bnh qun BMI kh tng ng.

2. Quan st mi quan h: PhysHlth ~ MentHlth

2.1 Boxplot/Violin plot: PhysHlth theo MentHlth

  • Khi MentHlth = 0 (tc khng ngy sc khe tinh thn km), median ca PhysHlth cng kh thp (~01).
  • Khi MentHlth tng dn (5, 10, 15), median ca PhysHlth c xu hng tng. Nhn boxplot:
    • MentHlth=10, median PhysHlth nhch ln khong 57
    • MentHlth=20, median PhysHlth ~10
    • MentHlth=30, median PhysHlth cn cao hn na (~15 hoc hn)
  • Nh vy, c v ngi c nhiu ngy sc khe tinh thn km thng km theo nhiu ngy sc khe th cht km.

2.2 Scatter plot: PhysHlth ~ MentHlth

  • D thy tng ct dc (theo MentHlth = 0, 1, 2 30) v hng ngang (theo PhysHlth = 0, 1, 2 30), v hai bin ny u l dng m trong [0..30].
  • ng hi quy c dc dng r hn so vi BMI ~ MentHlth/PhysHlth.
  • C th c h s tng quan (Spearman/Pearson) mc trung bnh hoc hn. Quan st biu Scatter Plot of PhysHlth and MentHlth cho thy cng MentHlth cao PhysHlth trung bnh cng cao.

Kt lun s b:

MentHlth v PhysHlth dng nh c mi lin h ng bin: khi s ngy gp vn v tinh thn tng, th s ngy th cht km cng tng.

3. Mt vi gi phn tch thng k su hn

  1. Kim nh tng quan
    • Vi bin m (030 ngy), dng Spearmans rank correlation c th ph hp hn Pearson.
    • K vng: \(\rho(\mathrm{MentHlth}, \mathrm{PhysHlth})\) > 0, c ngha thng k.
    • Trong khi \(\rho(\mathrm{MentHlth}, \mathrm{BMI})\) v \(\rho(\mathrm{PhysHlth}, \mathrm{BMI})\) c th rt nh (khng ngha hoc ngha yu).
  2. Phn tch thm
    • Nu mun, ta c th so snh trung bnh BMI gia cc nhm MentHlth/PhysHlth (VD: group = {0 ngy, >0 ngy}) qua t-test hoc Mann-Whitney. Tuy nhin, theo biu , khc bit s khng ln.
    • Cng c th phn tng (stratify) theo MentHlth/PhysHlth xem t l diabetes_012 hay t l high_BMI 30 khc nhau khng.
  3. Trong m hnh classification
    • MentHlth v PhysHlth c th (mt phn) trng lp thng tin v chng dng tng quan. C th ta cn regularization hoc tree-based model t chn ra bin mnh hn.
    • BMI nhn chung khng b ph thuc nhiu vo MentHlth/PhysHlth, nn khng lo a cng tuyn, nhng n l bin quan trng d on diabetes.

4. Kt lun

  • BMI gn nh khng i (hoc ch tng nh) khi MentHlth/PhysHlth tng: median quanh 2526, tri rng rt ln mi bin.
  • MentHlth v PhysHlth li c xu hng tng song song: khi MentHlth cao, PhysHlth trung bnh cng cao (hay ni cch khc, ngi gp vn tinh thn thng km th cht km).

T , trong cc bc phn tch hoc xy dng m hnh, ta c th:

  • Quan tm c bit n mi lin h MentHlthPhysHlth (c th bin ny ch ra nhm bnh nhn suy gim ton din c tinh thn ln th cht).
  • nh gi vai tr c lp ca BMI trong vic d bo tiu ng (v c th kt hp MentHlth, PhysHlth theo cch ph hp).
  • Lu rng MentHlth, PhysHlth vn l bin m (030) vi rt nhiu gi tr 0, nn cn chn m hnh/gii php x l ph hp (binning, transformation, zero-inflated approach, v.v.) nu dng chng lm bin ph thuc hoc predictor no trong m hnh thng k.

1. So snh BMI qua 3 nhm Diabetes_012

  • Nhm 0 (khng tiu ng):
    • Median BMI thng thp hn hai nhm cn li, mc khong 2526.
    • Di IQR tm [2230], v vn c nhiu outlier ln ti 70, 80, thm ch 100.
  • Nhm 1 (tin tiu ng):
    • Median BMI nhnh hn, khong 28.
    • Di IQR cng [2532], v vn c nhng outlier rt cao.
  • Nhm 2 (tiu ng):
    • Median BMI tim cn khong 2930, cao hn so vi nhm 0.
    • Tng t, outlier ko di n 90100.

Quan st ny ph hp vi hiu bit y khoa: ngi tin tiu ng / tiu ng thng c BMI cao hn trung bnh so vi ngi khng mc. D vy, phn phi BMI vn c tri rng ln trong tng nhm.

2. So snh MentHlth qua 3 nhm Diabetes_012

  • C 3 nhm u c median MentHlth nm rt thp (a s = 0), v phn ln ngi c kho st khng ghi nhn ngy tinh thn km.
  • D vy, ta vn bt gp nhng outlier ti 30 ngy c ba nhm.
  • Khc bit gia median cc nhm 0, 1, 2 c v rt nh; c th nhm 1 (tin tiu ng) hi cao hn mt cht so vi 0 v 2, nhng khng r rt.

Vy, s ngy tinh thn km (MentHlth) khng t ra khc bit ln gia ba nhm tiu ng. Nu c, c th l rt nh v cn kim nh thng k (nh KruskalWallis) xc nhn.

3. So snh PhysHlth qua 3 nhm Diabetes_012

  • Nhm 0: Median PhysHlth gn 01, IQR thp, nhng c nhiu outlier (mt s t ngi c 2030 ngy m).
  • Nhm 1: Median PhysHlth cao hn, khong 35 ngy km sc khe th cht.
  • Nhm 2: Median PhysHlth r rng cao nht, c th trn 56 ngy, IQR rng, v outlier ln ti 30 ngy.

Qua , c v nhm tiu ng (2) v nhm tin tiu ng (1) c xu hng gp nhiu ngy sc khe th cht km hn nhm khng tiu ng (0). S khc bit ny kh trc quan trn boxplot, cho thy tn sut ngy m cao hn ngi tin tiu ng v tiu ng.

4. Scatter Plot v mi lin h b ba: BMI, MentHlth, PhysHlth, Diabetes_012

  1. BMI ~ MentHlth, phn tch theo Diabetes_012
    • ng hi quy cho mi nhm (mu khc nhau) dc ln nh (tng quan yu gia BMI v MentHlth), trong nhm 2 (tiu ng) thng nm pha trn mt cht (BMI cao hn).
    • Ni chung, MentHlth tng khng ko theo BMI tng r rt, nhng ngi tiu ng (mu xanh) c BMI trung bnh cao hn hai nhm cn li.
  2. BMI ~ PhysHlth, phn tch theo Diabetes_012
    • Xu hng tng t: tng quan gia BMI v PhysHlth ch hi dng, dc rt nh.
    • Nhm 2 (tiu ng) vn nhnh hn v BMI trung bnh, ng thi PhysHlth cng cao hn.
  3. MentHlth ~ PhysHlth, phn tch theo Diabetes_012
    • C 3 ng hi quy (3 mu) u c dc dng: cng nhiu ngy tinh thn km, cng nhiu ngy th cht km.
    • ng ch , nhm 2 (tiu ng) dng nh c ng hi quy cao nht, ri n nhm 1, ri nhm 0. Cho thy ngi tiu ng va c MentHlth, PhysHlth cao hn trung bnh (ngy km nhiu), va c BMI cao hn.

5. Kt lun chnh

  1. BMI cao hn nhm 1 (tin tiu ng) v nhm 2 (tiu ng) so vi nhm 0, ph hp vi quan st lm sng (bo ph l yu t nguy c cho tiu ng).
  2. PhysHlth cho thy s phn tng r: nhm 2 > nhm 1 > nhm 0 (s ngy m nhiu nht ngi mc tiu ng).
  3. MentHlth khng khc bit nhiu gia cc nhm tiu ng, tuy nhin nhm 1 c median hi cao hn nhm 0, v nhm 2 th thp hn cht xu (c th do c mu hoc hnh vi bo co khc nhau).
  4. MentHlth v PhysHlth vn tng quan dng, v mc ny c v cao hn trong nhm tiu ng (ngi sc khe tinh thn km cng thng km th cht km).
  5. kim nh chnh thc, ta c th lm:
    • ANOVA / KruskalWallis cho s khc bit BMI gia 3 nhm Diabetes_012.
    • KruskalWallis cho MentHlth v PhysHlth (v bin m, nhiu zero). Nhng phn tch s b ny gi :
  • BMI l bin phn bit tt gia ngi c v khng c tiu ng.
  • PhysHlth cng c phn phi khc bit khi so snh nhm tiu ng vi nhm bnh thng.
  • MentHlth t c s chia r gia cc nhm tiu ng, song vn th hin tng quan vi PhysHlth trong c 3 nhm.

Tt c iu ny gip ta hiu r hn v c trng ca mi nhm v c c s xy dng m hnh phn loi (chng hn Random Forest, Logistic Regression, v.v.) vi BMI v PhysHlth (v cc bin khc) l predictor quan trng.

Chi Squared Test vi bin nh tnh

## Create a function to perform chi-square test and return results
chi_square_results <- lapply(qualitative_vars[qualitative_vars != "diabetes_012"], function(var) {
    contingency_table <- table(data[[var]], data$diabetes_012)
    chi_test <- chisq.test(contingency_table)
    
    data.frame(
        variable = var,
        chi_square = chi_test$statistic,
        df = chi_test$parameter,
        p_value = chi_test$p.value
    )
})
## Warning in stats::chisq.test(x, y, ...): Chi-squared approximation may be
## incorrect
## Combine results into a single dataframe
results_df <- do.call(rbind, chi_square_results)
results_df <- results_df |>
    arrange(desc(chi_square)) ##|>

## Create a function to perform chi-square test with Monte Carlo simulation
set.seed(42)
chi_square_results <- lapply(qualitative_vars[qualitative_vars != "diabetes_012"], function(var) {
    contingency_table <- table(data[[var]], data$diabetes_012)
    chi_test <- chisq.test(contingency_table, simulate.p.value = TRUE, B = 10000)
    
    data.frame(
        variable = var,
        chi_square = chi_test$statistic,
        ## df = chi_test$parameter,
        p_value = chi_test$p.value
    )
})

## Combine results into a single dataframe
results_df <- do.call(rbind, chi_square_results)
results_df <- results_df |>
    arrange(desc(chi_square)) |>
    mutate(
        signficance = case_when(
            p_value < 0.001 ~ "***",
            p_value < 0.01 ~ "**", 
            p_value < 0.05 ~ "*",
            TRUE ~ "ns"
        )
    )
